<h1>Settings Dialog</h1>
The settings dialog allows the user to change the general, algorithm, interface and database settings
<p>

<a href="#general">General tab</a><br/>
<a href="#algo">Algorithms tab</a><br/>
<a href="#ui">Interface tab</a><br/>
<a href="#db">Database tab</a><br/>
<p>


<a name="general">
<h3>General Settings</h3>
</a>
The general settings
<h4>Default File Dialog Locations</h4>
The default locations used by the image file dialogs
<ul>
<li>Default: The default system location</li>
<li>Last Opened: The last directory opened by the user</li>
<li>Custom: A custom file path</li>
</ul>


<a name="algo">
<h3>Algorithm Settings</h3>
</a>
The settings related to the algorithms used
<h4>GCP Detection</h4>
The GCP detection settings
<ul>
<li>Amount: The maximum number of GCPs to be detected</li>
<li>Band: The raster band used during the GCP extraction</li>
</ul>

<h4>GCP Chip</h4>
The GCP chip settings
<ul>
<li>Feature width: The width in pixels of the GCP chip that will be extracted</li>
<li>Feature height: The height in pixels of the GCP chip that will be extracted</li>
</ul>

<h4>RPC Model</h4>
The RPC model settings
<ul>
<li>RMS error threshold: The RMS error threshold used by the RPC model during the orthorectification process</li>
</ul>

<a name="ui">
<h3>Interface Settings</h3>
</a>
The settings for the user interface
<h4>Canvas</h4>
The canvas colors 
<ul>
<li>Reference canvas color: The background color for the reference canvas</li>
<li>Raw canvas color: The background color for the raw canvas</li>
</ul>

<h4>GCP Marker</h4>
The icon used to represent a GCP on the canvas
<ul>
<li>Marker icon: The icon used to represent a default GCP</li>
<li>Selected icon: The icon used to represent a GCP that is selected</li>
</ul>

<h4>Widget Visibility</h4>
Determines which widgets will be automatically loaded on startup
<ul>
<li>GCP table startup: The GCP table will automatically be loaded on startup if checked</li>
<li>Reference image startup: The reference canvas will automatically be loaded on startup if checked</li>
<li>Raw image startup: The raw canvas will automatically be loaded on startup if checked</li>
</ul>


<a name="db">
<h3>Database Settings</h3>
</a>
The settings for the databases
<h4>General</h4>
General database settings
<h5>Database usage</h5>
Sets the type of database used for GCP storage and retrieval
<ul>
<li>None: No database will be used</li>
<li>SQLite: A SQLite database will be used</li>
<li>Postgres: A PostgreSQL database will be used</li>
</ul>

<h5>Load GCPs</h5>
Detemines how GCPs should be loaded from database when available
<ul>
<li>Always: GCPs are automatically loaded if detected in the database</li>
<li>Ask: The user will be prompted if GCPs were detected in the database</li>
<li>Never: GCPs are never loaded from the database. The user has to manually request them.</li>
</ul>

<h4>SQLite</h4>
SQLite specific configurations
<h5>File path</h5>
<ul>
<li>Default: The default system location</li>
<li>Custom: A custom file path</li>
</ul>

<h4>Postgres</h4>
Postgres specific configuration
<ul>
<li>Database name: The name of the database</li>
<li>Username: The username for the database</li>
<li>Password: The password for the database</li>
<li>Host: The location of the database</li>
</ul>
